The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 0.1 percent to 33,948.48.  Bank stocks followed global equities lower after French
President  Nicolas Sarkozy  said his nation and  Germany  will
propose a financial transaction tax.  Grupo Financiero Banorte SAB (GFNORTEO MM) dropped 2
percent to 44.09 pesos.  Grupo Financiero Inbursa SA (GFINBURO)  , the financial services firm controlled by billionaire
 Carlos Slim , retreated 2.9 percent to 24.28 pesos.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, rose 2.9 percent to 6.99 pesos. Manufacturers in the
U.S. produced more cars, computers and furniture in July. The
0.9 percent increase in output at factories, mines and utilities
was almost twice the median forecast of economists surveyed by
Bloomberg and the biggest gain of the year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
